üîπ Blue Prism

‚úÖ Pros
	‚Ä¢	Enterprise-grade: Built specifically for large-scale automation in regulated industries (banking, insurance, healthcare).
	‚Ä¢	Scalable & Robust: Strong centralized control room, queue management, and scheduling for thousands of bots.
	‚Ä¢	Security & Compliance: Audit logs, role-based access, encryption ‚Äì trusted by enterprises with strict governance.
	‚Ä¢	Reusable Objects: Encourages structured design with reusable business objects and processes.
	‚Ä¢	Integration Depth: Can integrate with legacy applications (Citrix, mainframes, Windows apps) very well.

‚ùå Cons
	‚Ä¢	Cost: Licensing is expensive compared to Power Automate.
	‚Ä¢	Complex Setup: Requires server setup, database, and IT involvement for infra.
	‚Ä¢	Learning Curve: Development follows a more technical approach (object/process modeling).
	‚Ä¢	Limited AI/ML Built-in: Needs third-party tools for AI/ML (e.g., OCR, sentiment analysis).
	‚Ä¢	Cloud-Native Features: Less agile compared to Microsoft‚Äôs ecosystem for quick cloud-based solutions.

