üîπ Power Automate (Microsoft)

‚úÖ Pros
	‚Ä¢	Cost-Effective: Lower entry cost, especially for organizations already using Microsoft 365.
	‚Ä¢	Cloud-Native: Easy to start (no infra setup) with connectors for 500+ apps (Outlook, Teams, SharePoint, Dynamics).
	‚Ä¢	AI Builder: Prebuilt AI models for forms processing, sentiment analysis, object detection.
	‚Ä¢	Citizen Development: Business users can build simple flows without deep technical skills.
	‚Ä¢	Integration with Microsoft Ecosystem: Seamless with Azure, Office 365, and Dynamics 365.
	‚Ä¢	Hybrid (Cloud + Desktop): Supports both cloud flows and desktop automation (via Power Automate Desktop).

‚ùå Cons
	‚Ä¢	Enterprise Scalability: Not as strong as Blue Prism in large-scale centralized bot management.
	‚Ä¢	Security & Control: Still improving in governance and auditability compared to Blue Prism.
	‚Ä¢	Performance: Desktop automation can be slower/less stable for complex legacy apps.
	‚Ä¢	Licensing Complexity: Per-user/per-flow plans can get confusing at scale.
	‚Ä¢	Advanced Dev Flexibility: Less control for building highly customized automations compared to Blue Prism.
